  "title": "The Divorced Dad's Guide to Slaying Vampires",
  "description": "From the playwright that brought you \"Musical for the Endtimes\" and the director of \"Sweet Jesus: The Gospel According to Felt.\" A punchy new comedy about fatherhood (and fighting vampires). Kevin, a recently divorced Dad, must fight to free St. Albert from Dracula's fascist regime.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Matthew Hackett<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Ben Osgood<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Colin Bluekens, Alexandra Lepage, Aidan Laudersmith, Jackson Card, Rowan Andruik, Marshall Eglinski, Sheldon Stockdale, Randy Brososky<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Amy Dass, Matthew Anderson, Shane Marsh<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Liora Friedland<br/>",
  "website": "https://www.instagram.com/divorceddadvsvampires",
  "plain_language": "In St. Albert, vampires take over the city. Kevin, a divorced dad and former punk rocker, teams up with his daughter’s friends, Sarah and Finley, to fight the vampires and save the people. Kevin also tries to help his old bandmate Brad, who is Finley’s dad. They all face their fears and family problems. The show has original punk music by Edmonton band FOOLS.",
